@node not04 "PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART X"
                         PAYBACK STATUS REPORT: PART X
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

23 April 2000 - The Latest News

There's been a lot of progress this month, although most of it has involved
designing new missions. Anyway, here's what I've been up to since last time:

   - Different types of terrain now offer varying levels of grip.
   - People now have shadows.
   - Motion blurring is now supported.
   - Memory allocation has been made more efficient, reducing the game's
     footprint by 4 Mb, allowing the game to run confortably on a 16 Mb Amiga.
     As a side effect of this, the game also loads slightly quicker.
   - Explanatory text now appears on screen when you pick up bonuses, gain score
     or lose health.
   - The gameplay has been extensively tweaked and lots of bugs have been fixed.
   - More missions have been written and more of the city has been designed. In
     fact, this forms the bulk of the work done this month.
   - Due to popular demand, it's now possible to handbrake turn your vehicle -
     which is especially fun if you happen to be driving a bus!
   - Decorative objects, such as cones and barriers, have been added.

Well, that's all for this updated. See you next time!

James Daniels
Apex Designs

For more information about Payback, visit
http://www.apex-designs.net/payback.html.
