I'm not a graphics artist. My drawing skills are very limited. So, when my
partner in crime told me that he wanted to overhaul the SAUG website I was very
happy. At the end, the website was going to have a sexy new look :)

If you have ever visited the webpage, you would have seen its simple look.
That's why I didn't care of how it looks with Amiga browsers. But now, I known
how bad they work.

First, Voyager 3.2 which has been released this month. It has problems with
nested tables (it gurues) and it is very sloooooooooow displaying them. Because
of this, it takes some time to display the main page of the WEB.

Ibrowse 2.2 is probably the fastest browser at the Amiga. It does not have
problems with tables, but colours. The background colour at the WEB page is
blue-ish, but IBrowse display as a purple-ish. 

And finally, AWeb 3.3SE (which is included in the OS3.5 distribution) has the
same problem with the background colours as IBrowse, and besides it does not
support the <TABLE ALIGN=CENTER> tag. Bufff.

I can't help to say that Netscape 4.7 and Ibrowse 5.0 are better browsers.

Remember to visit the SAUG website, which is located in:

        http://www.saug.org/

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

        noticias@saug.org

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

